{"questionId":"9074970","questionHtml":"<p>Unpolarized light of intensity <em>I<sub>0</sub></em> is incident on a polarizing filter. Light from this filter is incident on&nbsp;a second filter, which has its axis of polarization at 30˚ to that of the first filter.</p>\n<p>The value of cos 30˚ is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{\\sqrt 3 }}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>. What is the intensity of the light emerging through the second filter?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{\\sqrt 3 }}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I<sub>0</sub></em></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{3}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I<sub>0</sub></em></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{3}{4}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I<sub>0</sub></em></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{3}{8}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>8</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I<sub>0</sub></em></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074970","referenceCode":"17N.1.HL.TZ0.12","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Unpolarized light of intensity I0 is incident on a polarizing filter. Light from this filter is incident on a second filter, which has its axis of polarization at 30˚ to that of th","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"12","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics","3.2 – Modelling a gas","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}